The R² gap between Model A and Model B quantifies how much runtime variance requires runtime-observable signals to explain but does not capture the gap from memory bandwidth constraints versus compute constraints. The roofline model is used to address the gap directly by establishing theoretical peak performance bounds for neural network operators relative to the T4 hardware ceilings. The achievable operational throughput of an operator is limited by the minimum between the peak computational throughput of the accelerator or the product of the accelerator’s memory bandwidth and arithmetic intensity AI. 
